But when a Chriſtian arrives to the end of his Heavenly Journey, the Angels ſtand ready to carry him into Abraham's Boſom; 

                     •
                  ake 16.22. then Chriſt he uſhers them into the Preſence of his Father. Is it not a great Honour for a Subject to be brought by the King's Son into his Father's Preſence; and there tells him what a good Subject he hath been to him; and thus and thus hath he done for me, reward him as it ſeems in thy Pleaſure? So Chriſt takes his faithful Servant, and brings him to the Preſence of his Father, tells him what Gain he hath made of his Talent, and deſires him that he may enter into the Joy of his Maſter.
